website_summaries.verdict: While the tackle box leaves a bit to be desired, the lures themselves are a good, sturdy assortment that are also kind to the environment.
pros: 100-piece set that includes everything from spinnerbaits and topwater frogs to sinker weights and hooks that come in 3 different sizes
Lures are crafted from TPR, an environmentally friendly material
Comes with a double-level tackle box
cons: The jig hooks are particularly thin and break easily when hooking fish
Some reports of the box arriving broken

customer_reviews.title: Registered Maine Guide Approved
customer_reviews.text: What an awesome lure, the action and movement of the legs and the pop of the body and how it sits in the water it might as well be a live frog! I had one leg come off and I contacted the company and they sent me a replacement without batting an eye. As a registered Maine guide I am always looking to showcase products and get my clients the most success possible! Pickerel, bass and muskies slam these lures HARD!
customer_reviews.author: Joanna Liberatore

customer_reviews.title: Great lures
customer_reviews.text: These lures were fabulous for catching bass. My sons were able to have an enjoyable day of fishing using these lures. They are easy to use and are very appealing to the bass. I would definitely recommend these for anyone wanting to catch the big one.
customer_reviews.author: Melissa Santos

customer_reviews.title: strong and realistic!
customer_reviews.text: So far so good on these lures! they are very realistic looking so i have high hopes that the fish will think so too lol. They are high quality and i have tugged hard on a few hooks on ones i didn't forsee using for the type of fishing we do. The hooks stay tight! No stretch or tearing. I haven't been able to go out with them yet as the weather decided to flip and start snowing in march but i hope to get out and fully utilize them soon! I'll update it if i find any problems but my guess is they are going to work great!
customer_reviews.author: Werebunnies

customer_reviews.title: Great lures
customer_reviews.text: Great frogs. Bass love them. Can’t find colors like this anywhere. Durable and they work great for buzzing across top water or swimming them on bottom. I would recommend to any bass fisherman.
customer_reviews.author: C. West

customer_reviews.title: Nice little variety tackle set
customer_reviews.text: Nice little variety tackle set. I ordered the 78 piece set and it provides everything pictured. A nice assortment of little weights, sturdy hooks, and false worms for a day fishing trip to the lake or river. Multiple color iptions on the false works for different lighting settings. love the little frog lure, especially excited to get out and try her out. Will update with video from out in the field fishing.
customer_reviews.author: Squirrel Master

customer_reviews.title: Can work well
customer_reviews.text: Very good action and very similar to top name brands as far as the top colors go. The belly on all were the same color which is what the fish see.That's not a bad thing if you were to buy 5 frogs of the same belly color, this is cheaper. I'm planing on air bushing the bellies close to the top color (or adjacent to the top) to make them different. Plastics is very soft, so hook set shouldn't be much of an issue and some slight modifications to widen the hooks outwards will benefit the hookup ratio.
customer_reviews.author: Gary 0765Top Contributor: Photography

customer_reviews.title: Nice set for my 8 year old
customer_reviews.text: I am not a fishing expert by any means, so I cannot attest to the quality or practicality of this set as expected at the purchase price. However, as a parent of an 8 year old who is very much interested in fishing, I am happy to report that his reaction alone was well worth the price. The case appears to be solid and practical, and the jam-packed contents appear to satisfy the needs of a novice - and most likely those with more experience. Communication with RUNCL was also excellent and it was clear that they stand firmly behind this product. I would purchase this set again if I ever took up fishing myself.
customer_reviews.author: W. Kim

customer_reviews.title: Awesome Product
customer_reviews.text: Awesome product! The frog looks real. I have only tried to fish with it few times. I have had few hits on it but I set the hook too early. I think I need more practice with this lure.
customer_reviews.author: Troy

customer_reviews.title: Good quality, plastic storage box included
customer_reviews.text: They seem to be good quality. I tried using them for a little while, but I didn’t have any weedless hooks. I picked up some hooks, and plan to use these next time. I included a picture of how I set them up on the hook. Since my original review, I have gotten many strikes on these. I was only able to hook 2. One was a small mouth bass, and the other was a pickerel.
customer_reviews.author: Tyler Durden

customer_reviews.title: Don’t get these.
customer_reviews.text: At first glance these frogs look great. But, I used one today. First first I caught with it, the frog was pretty much destroyed. The hooks pulled out and I was unable to get then to go back into where they are supposed to sit. The hooks also dig into the sides of the frog. While these look tempting, I would stay away from these and get the better quality brand version for a few dollars more.
customer_reviews.author: Glen

customer_reviews.title: Not a bad set for the price
customer_reviews.text: I got this kit on a lightning deal. Overall they're pretty good baits. It could use a bit tighter seals around the legs/tassels. I had to squeeze water out every couple of casts to keep them floating. I've had some strikes on the one with legs and the one with a carbon fiber look, but haven't landed anything yet. I'll try them some more this upcoming season.
customer_reviews.author: B.T.S.Top Contributor: Gardening

customer_reviews.title: Not bad!!
customer_reviews.text: Just received them today so this review is based on presentation only. I’ll update after first time using them. Presentation is like all the other reviews they’re pretty awesome looking. Just the right softness to allow proper hook sets. Color is close to real looking without actually being real So based on first impression I’d say take a chance and try them Update July 26 Didn’t get the action i was hoping based on other reviews. Maybe just a bad day. But so far no great attacks
customer_reviews.author: Jack Caruso

customer_reviews.title: Great for the price
customer_reviews.text: These frogs are hard to beat for the price. They float well and catch bass, but not sure how durrable they wil be. If you want a different color belly, use scented markers. While the hooks are sharp, they are not as sturdy as on more expensive models, but I've landed bass to 6.25 lbs. and not bent them out. With these deals, I got 10 frogs for the price of 2 better brands. If you are fishing for hogs, use the sturdier brands, but these do work pretty well.
customer_reviews.author: Ted Baker

customer_reviews.title: The real performing frog!
customer_reviews.text: Who wants to catch bass? Who wants a lure that does a great job and performs better than other lures in its class? I do, that's who. And that is what I got when I purchased these top water frog lures! This is one of the most realistic frogs I have ever seen in the water (other than real frogs of course). The look is realistic, the retrieve is smooth, and I recommend this to anyone who wants to experience a toad of a bass hitting this frog!! What are you waiting for? Scroll back up from this review and get a real lure that preforms!!
customer_reviews.author: Shannon

customer_reviews.title: They Sink and require much adjustment!!!
customer_reviews.text: They are much smaller than expected. Other brands state the size in the specs. These frogs lool good and are soft. Hooks are lighter gauge than better brands and are ot bent evenly. The worse part is that they will submerge before you retrieve halfway. You will need to do a bit of hook bending and hole sealing and then these will be fine.
customer_reviews.author: TWO CENT

customer_reviews.title: Good diversity in lures for beginning fisherman, but box hinge came broken!
customer_reviews.text: The Lure box contained everything a new fisher would need to get going. I got the 100 piece box and everything was there as advertised. My only gripe is that the box itself was not very sturdy and the clear plastic middle section (that connects to the lid) had actually broken during shipping. The small joints that connect it to the lid had snapped during shipping, so the middle section of my box had come completely loose. It's still functional, but annoying to open and close now.
customer_reviews.author: Amanda L

customer_reviews.title: Great swim motion
customer_reviews.text: Took them out this weekend Friday and today. Best luck I have had with top water yet. I had 8 big blow ups, 4 that spit the hook and 3 Bass caught. I never tried the frog before but went to a grassy spot and couldn't fish anything else with getting caught up. I hate that I have had more luck with frogs than 50 dollars in other lures. The quality is fine for the price I even gave my buddy 2 of them to try because he got his crank bait stuck. He even looked it up. They were easy to learn the swim motion that got the most bites.
customer_reviews.author: LennyKaps

customer_reviews.title: If it looks like a frog but doesn’t move like a frog, is it still a frog?
customer_reviews.text: One hit on the dark green lure and he is living out the rest of his life with a gimp leg. I was not impressed with how the frogs swam and have used more expensive frog lures that legit move just like a frog. These just aren’t those kind of lures. Don’t get me wrong, you can still catch fish on them, I just wasn’t impressed.
customer_reviews.author: J. Shelley

customer_reviews.title: Nice looking lures, but some will sink
customer_reviews.text: These lures looks great. The organizer is nice too. Finally had a chance to try them out. They are indeed snag free and glide/swim right through weeds. However, 2 of the frogs filled with water and then sank on their first cast, which totally ruins the action of the lure. Thus the low rating. I’m going to try filling the sinking frogs with stryofoam.
customer_reviews.author: Mike

customer_reviews.title: Look nice but don't work so well
customer_reviews.text: Was excited to get these to try out this weekend. Well I hooked it up and threw it out.. After the second cast iit sank. Reeled it back up. Its full of water.. Squeeze it and the water shoots out and is good for 2 cast before it sinks again. Tried a different one. Same thing.. I have used other hollow body frogs and they never did this so often, if at all. Due to this issue I can not give it a high rating. But they look good, Hooks are sharp and when they work they work well..
customer_reviews.author: Jimmyb

customer_reviews.title: Good value.
customer_reviews.text: These are great for Large Mouth Bass. It is a multi use type of bait. Can be Texas rigged, Carolina, or even Drop Shot application. A great overall bait. Would highly recommend!
customer_reviews.author: "jb"

customer_reviews.title: Really love this lure set
customer_reviews.text: Really love this lure set. The design is so nice and the bag is small enough for me to carry it around with no problem. The quality looks pretty good too and I would definitely recommend it. Item is just as described and arrived on time.
customer_reviews.author: Mina

customer_reviews.title: Great lures
customer_reviews.text: The fish cann’t stay away from it. Great soft plastics love them.
customer_reviews.author: Troy

customer_reviews.title: Not satisfied
customer_reviews.text: 1 out if the 5 had a defective hook. Was bent so far down it would have missed every time. These also take on a lot of water which defeat the purpose. You cant have to keep squeezing them after every cast. It’s a nuisance. (If you don’t squeeze them, they sink and don't float/pop) The hollow body moves too easy. Just like taking on water i had to adjust the body on the hook frame frequently.
customer_reviews.author: Dave

customer_reviews.title: Strong material that catches fish
customer_reviews.text: Colors are very life like. Great weight ratio to help with long precise cast. I caught a few bass and a snakehead on them and there are no damage to them. Even after the snakehead hit it and spit it to hit it again. The streamers are well made as well I don't see them melting on a hot day like some of my other brand frog lures. They did their job and caught me a few fish and stayed together in the process I definitely recommend.
customer_reviews.author: ben suber

customer_reviews.title: Hooks were crooked and narrow.
customer_reviews.text: The frogs are decent. 5 for 13 bucks isn’t bad at all. I like the fact that you get a variety of frogs as well as different belly colors of the frog. My only complaint is the hooks. Some of my frogs had hooks that were not fitted to the frog’s body. Some were too narrow while others were crooked. Some people might have to bend the hooks to straighten them out for better hook ratio.
customer_reviews.author: Lokkstar

customer_reviews.title: Kid tested
customer_reviews.text: Pretty tough but not the best action. My son played with these a lot and only ripped a few. One bass so far with these
customer_reviews.author: Jasseu

customer_reviews.title: Great frog lure, realistic design.
customer_reviews.text: This is a great frog lure for any bass fisherman. The color is very natural and realistic, and there are many different colors and styles to choose from. It comes in a simple package and was in good condition. It is well weighted and floats perfectly. The presentation on your retrieve is very realistic. Topwaters are my favorite bass lure because they are so exciting to use, and this frog is no different. The hook sets very effectively on a good bite and I had no trouble bringing the lure through brush and right into the fish's mouth. I would recommend this lure for any angler that wants to fish thick cover.
customer_reviews.author: Tyler Knapp

customer_reviews.title: Look very cheap. I guess you get what you pay for
customer_reviews.text: 1st impression “ they suck”. The hooks were not centered. One of them looked used, paint was peeling off before I opened the packet. Will update later after I fish with them. Update: had to change from 2 stars to a 1. After every 1 or 2 cast you have to adjust the hooks and the body of the frogs. The bad part was this was in very little cover.
customer_reviews.author: Jeff

customer_reviews.title: Container broke but lures are good!
customer_reviews.text: The hooks, weights, and lures were in good condition when shipped in. The hooks aren't super durable but they'll do and it's still a great deal for the price. However, the container they came in was broken during shipping. The backside broke off so the materials (weights and hooks) fell out. I had to throw out the container but thankfully I bought a tackle box separately with other containers to put them in.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Get what you pay for...sigh
customer_reviews.text: Popper front should be firm, doesn't make a great pop and the rubber frog fills with water after most cast (1-2). The positioning of the hooks are off on them. Out of the container 3 of the 5 had to be moved so the skirt legs weren't caught. Color is great on these but the quality is not good.
customer_reviews.author: Eneill75

customer_reviews.title: Great quality fishing set
customer_reviews.text: My son was so excited to get this set. The items in the set are great quality and I was very pleased with the set. The items are very easy to use and even my 6 year old daughter was able to use them with ease.
customer_reviews.author: Melissa Santos

customer_reviews.title: Holy Stinking Lures...
customer_reviews.text: These things stink, the claim if PVC should be PVA as "Acetate" odor is so prominent I'm trying to figure out how to remove it. The hooks are not aligned with the bodies and the are connected to a swivel thing that protrudes from the nose. $10 seems like a good deal till they arrive and you inspect and the smell hit you.
customer_reviews.author: Phillip Reedy

customer_reviews.title: Decent quality
customer_reviews.text: I used one practicing in the yard. Beat the heck out of it for a couple hours ...doesn't look like its been beat up!. Only one has a yellowish bottom the others are white. Haven't caught anything yet...still learning freshwater fishing but that could be me
customer_reviews.author: Kenny

customer_reviews.title: Good Value
customer_reviews.text: This frog variety pack is a great value. The material that they are made of is a 6.5/10 in my eyes. hooks are better than I expected when I purchased. Fills with water a little bit quicker than the major brands but that is to be expected for the price. Colors are pretty nice as well.
customer_reviews.author: Paul Beemsterboer

customer_reviews.title: Real Frogs
customer_reviews.text: Just received frogs! Looks very real compared to other one I've been using. Legs seem kinds of skinny though and little smaller than expected. Will test it out and update review later.
customer_reviews.author: Austin

customer_reviews.title: decent product for the price point, however do not recommend!!
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these frogs a year ago and my biggest complaint about them is that they leak. Water easily enters the drain hole and causes the frogs to sink. Also the frog's shape makes the auction not as effective as other popper frogs. With these complaints I would not recommend unless your'e on a tight budget.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great value!
customer_reviews.text: Cant beat it for the price, these are definitely a cheaper frog but hooks are nice and sharp, comes with a hard plastic case to store them or other lures in and I really like how the belly sides are all different colors unlike alot of lures where they're just all white! Highly recommend!
customer_reviews.author: sean

customer_reviews.title: the rubber on these is very thin
customer_reviews.text: I think I would have been better to buy more expensive frogs. The material in these felt about 1/3 the weight, (thickness) of a frog that I paid $10 for one frog. I have not used them yet for fishing so don't know how they will hold up especially catching a fish with teeth.
customer_reviews.author: Carroll B

customer_reviews.title: NO ACTION
customer_reviews.text: The legs don't move and look unnatural as I reeled in my line. Didn't catch a thing
customer_reviews.author: KitchenKutter

customer_reviews.title: Good frogs
customer_reviews.text: These are just as detailed as the pictures show. Haven't put them out in the lily pads yet, but they look promising. Not sure if it's mentioned in the description, but there's even a small weight in the soft body so these should sit back side down like a real frog as well.
customer_reviews.author: Nathan Waters

customer_reviews.title: Great frogs for the money!
customer_reviews.text: I bought these because I was tired of buying those $8 lunker frogs and losing them. These are a great alternative and much, much cheaper. I tied one on, went outside and caught 2 bass from the 3 test casts I made. These seem to hook up better than most frogs as well!
customer_reviews.author: Clayton

customer_reviews.title: Only worth two frogs!
customer_reviews.text: Two frogs are fantastic. I had great success out of the green dble tail w/yellow and red belly and the grey popper frog. the legs fell out of the frog w/out a hit and they should pay you for the yellow popper. don't bother tying it on.
customer_reviews.author: Brian Dreiling

customer_reviews.title: Dare You to Catch a Weed!
customer_reviews.text: My canal is covered in weeds and has been making fishing so aggravating. Then I found these awesome frog lures. I can cast on top of the weeds and pull it through, without a snag. I can cast the lure on the opposite bank and slowly drop it in, so as not to cause a big splash - no weeds/grass! Works like a charm. Now, my only problem.....I haven't caught a fish yet. I'm still optimistic, because I love the hook placement, which never fouls in the weeds.
customer_reviews.author: Fred

customer_reviews.title: FIVE STARS
customer_reviews.text: These frogs hands down catch fish! Whether your a beginner or pro these frogs will catch you a fish. I use them 1-3 times a week and solely have a rod set aside for one of these frogs! Thank you guys for continuing to put out great product! I highly suggest this item
customer_reviews.author: Max plambeck

customer_reviews.title: Good frog lures
customer_reviews.text: Frogs were as described. Good value for the money, sharp hooks, decent colors. Floats well and heavy enough to cast far. If you have never used frog lures before, I would suggest you get some. You can cast right into a patch of weeds, and reel right out of them due to the weedless nature of frog design, which also means you will get lots of strikes, so be patient and give the fish 2-3 seconds to get it in their mouth before you set the hook.
customer_reviews.author: john h allen

customer_reviews.title: Great quality for the price
customer_reviews.text: These are awesome! I've bought single frogs that cost the same as this pack. Never again! Paint quality is great and theyre weighted right. Seriously, give them a chance. Ive caught several largemouths with these.
customer_reviews.author: Kyle V.

customer_reviews.title: Best gf ever in life.
customer_reviews.text: I went looking for these after I saw the prices my bf was paying for similar lures in bait shops and in the big box stores. He fishes everyday and he said these frogs are the exact lures he buys in-store, but I saved almost 75% buying them on Amazon. Next day delivery to boot, this one was a no-brainer. He couldn't be happier.... with me, or the lures 😊.
customer_reviews.author: Beaglejuice

customer_reviews.title: Caught many 5lb+ bass with these
customer_reviews.text: These things work great. The legs will rip off pretty quickly, maybe after a few fish. I've fished them without the legs for a long time and they honestly work better without the legs anyway because you don't miss the fish who are just hitting the leg of the frog. Only downside is that the weight will fall out eventually, so the frog will sink a little if you don't fish it fast enough. Still work good, or just put a little tiny bit of super glue around the weight initially.
customer_reviews.author: Ryan

customer_reviews.title: Don’t bother
customer_reviews.text: These r junk . Figured I’d try but don’t bother. If they don’t sink have fun casting and reeling in your line with knot still tied on but frog not there lol... pops right out
customer_reviews.author: Matt W

customer_reviews.title: The frog lures offer a good variety of color and they work well so far.
customer_reviews.text: These frog lures are catching bass, especially around weed cover in our lake. The lures are well made, although I've only used them 3 times so far. All in all, a good purchase.
customer_reviews.author: musicman

customer_reviews.title: So realistic...
customer_reviews.text: So realistic that my 13 year old daughter could barely resist biting it. I handed it to her and she almost bit it before realizing that would be a bad idea. Have yet to catch a bass on one yet tho does seem to move well in the water and threw fairly heavy cover without snagging up too bad
customer_reviews.author: Josh Wilson

customer_reviews.title: Ok lure, great value.
customer_reviews.text: Great price. Not very lifelike swimming. Not a single hit from fish in a spot that other frogs incite big blow-ups on. Not sure I'd recommend for catching fish. But very durable and a great way to learn frogging.
customer_reviews.author: Samuel Maeder

customer_reviews.title: Don't waste your money on these
customer_reviews.text: To start off these are terrible. I recieved my order in the condition of the pictures. One came without the tail plug and was punctured on the side by the hook. The one with the legs was also punctured by the hook. None of them have any kind of seal to prevent water from entering the point where the hooks come out the belly and once they take on water they just sink. Worthless. Don't waste your money on these
customer_reviews.author: Nathan baker

customer_reviews.title: Nice little frog package!!
customer_reviews.text: My frogs arrived on time and in great shape. The frogs were the ones in the description and are in a nice case. I fished 2 of them today and caught a couple of largemouth bass. The hooks are sharp and they walk well. I would recommend.
customer_reviews.author: James Norris

customer_reviews.title: Great Frogs!!! 5 for the price of 1!!!
customer_reviews.text: These frogs are a great value, they are made very well and with razor sharp hooks. They are right on par with the $10-$15 Googan/Strike King frogs except you get 5 frogs for the price of the others 1 frog. On top of that they come with their own case 👌🏼 Another excellent product from RUNCL!!! Well worth the pruchase.
customer_reviews.author: TimothyN

customer_reviews.title: Received 2 of same color
customer_reviews.text: 2 of the 5 “assorted colors” were the same color. I wanted a replacement but that option wasn’t available, only to return it. I like them and wanted to try them out this weekend but the feeling of being jipped and inconvenienced has me thinking otherwise. And now I go another weekend without
customer_reviews.author: Andrew James Estrada

customer_reviews.title: Great Frogs. Hard to find in stores & great price.
customer_reviews.text: I’ve bought these frogs twice now. They are top notch. They have features that you just can’t find in stores. For example there is one of them that has a little spoon on the bottom to add some extra flash, and another is a super rare grey that catches huge fish. The one legged frog is just like a LH. I would recommend to anyone who loves top water blowups. Which is everyone.
customer_reviews.author: C. West

customer_reviews.title: Bigger than expected
customer_reviews.text: Way bigger then expected.. too large for me. Will return
customer_reviews.author: Dee Smith

customer_reviews.title: These look like great toowater lures
customer_reviews.text: These look like great toowater lures. I got them out on a local pond recently but was too cold, so no bites. Just wanted to see how their action was on top water and they were perfect. After a while some water got in them and just needed to be released. Other than that I can’t wait for the warmer weather.
customer_reviews.author: Alexander C.

customer_reviews.title: they seem pretty decent. Caught a small large mouth on the ...
customer_reviews.text: So far 2 out of 3 that ive used start sinking after a couple casts. Other than having to squeeze the water out of the 2 every couple casts, they seem pretty decent. Caught a small large mouth on the gray one the first time i used it
customer_reviews.author: Jlwillis

customer_reviews.title: NICELY MADE
customer_reviews.text: A DIVERSE FROG LURE PACKAGE...HOPE TO TEST THEM SOON AS THE LAKE THAWS OUT...THE FISH ARE WAITING TOO...REALISTIC MARKINGS ON THE LURES ARE SURE TO ATTRACT THE BIG ONES.
customer_reviews.author: Tudy Gordon

customer_reviews.title: Very realistic
customer_reviews.text: My husband loves these lures. I was surprised at how realistic they are. He says they work well. One fell apart pretty quickly but the rest have held up great.
customer_reviews.author: Kiki

customer_reviews.title: Great quality soft frogs
customer_reviews.text: Great quality soft frogs. They are all painted excellent and feel really high quality. If anything negative, the strings hanging from the backs are a bit long but can be cut to whatever length you desire with scissors. Great lures for the price, especially since you get 5 for about the price of 2.
customer_reviews.author: Joseph Taper

customer_reviews.title: Goos.
customer_reviews.text: Had a chance to take them out on the water. Lures are great cannot beat the price. Cast out far and great action. Take in very minimal water.
customer_reviews.author: William M.

customer_reviews.title: Not like the pictures. You get what you paid for I guess.
customer_reviews.text: Paint is messed up.. random splatters all over them. And 3 of the 5 that we got had bent hooks and cannot be fixed. And they smell awful.
customer_reviews.author: Sarah Bilyeu

customer_reviews.title: If your looking for excellent quality frogs, BUY THESE!!
customer_reviews.text: Just received these today and I can already tell they are top quality. Another excellent product from an excellent company!
customer_reviews.author: James Hinds

customer_reviews.title: Lifelike
customer_reviews.text: Just got them the other day, haven’t had a chance to splash any yet, however, I’m very impressed by their lifelike appearance. Also, they have a very soft body, exposing the hooks very easily. Legs seem durable, but we all know how that goes, the Bass are ruthless on those appendages 😳 Hope to fish them soon, and plan to update my review, but for know I give them 👍👍
customer_reviews.author: Andy

customer_reviews.title: Too bad they don’t perform as good as they look.
customer_reviews.text: These are great looking frog lures! But upon fishing them, these frogs do not float! They’re not durable either. I now know why they were priced so low.
customer_reviews.author: Gregory

customer_reviews.title: good quality frogs
customer_reviews.text: Just received the frogs today but the box that holds the frogs in is cracked and pieces of the plastic broke off. Sort of disappointed since it stated that it would've arrived on Saturday 13th, but after I ordered the date changed and did not receive it until today (Sunday 14th). Overall, can't wait to try these out.
customer_reviews.author: Quang

customer_reviews.title: Cheap
customer_reviews.text: Great value but you get what you pay for. Material is really thin. Have had 2 rip after single catch. I didn’t intend for them to be disposable lures. They work, you will catch fish but I won’t buy again.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Awesome!
customer_reviews.text: Bought these when I first got into bass fishing. Just bought my second pack. (2 years later)
customer_reviews.author: Brandon

customer_reviews.title: Worth every penny!
customer_reviews.text: The lures, rigs, hooks, jigs are all of good design and work great for fresh water fishing in all conditions of weather and water clarity. I'm very happy with the performance of all pieces and its a great value for all levels of outdoorsmen. A good deal for sure, you'd pay much more at a fishing or outdoor store.
customer_reviews.author: Aiz

customer_reviews.title: not impressed
customer_reviews.text: These frogs are very skinny, don't float well, and have finicky action. It was difficult to get fish to bite and the hookup ratio was poor. I prefer just about any other topwater frog.
customer_reviews.author: YetiJedi

Perfect Angle Sitting: The core of gravity for RUNCL frog lures are constantly checked to ensure best angle sitting inside the water, helps with the success of hook up
Weedless Design: With hooks embedded into the belly of the frogs, helps to expose the hooks better when the fish strikes, and no concern whatsoever about hanging up by lily pads or weed beds
